Peru Aims to Slash Coca Crop 20% by 2016, El Peruano Reports

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-11-29T14:47:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/peru-aims-to-slash-coca-crop-20-by-2016-el-peruano-reports.html
Peru aims to reduce its coca crop by
20 percent within five years to stem rising cocaine production,
El Peruano  reported , citing the government’s drugs czar, Ricardo Soberon.  The Andean nation’s coca crop will be cut back to 48,000
hectares by 2016 from 60,100 hectares now, Soberon said,
according to the state-owned newspaper.  Peru will host a June 26-27 summit of drug czars from South
America, the U.S., Canada and the European Union, El Peruano
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 